OL,3,CGovernment pledges to 'transform care'
OL,4,Cfor people with ME
OL,6,FThe Government has pledged to give
OL,7,Fhundreds of thousands of people living
OL,8,Fwith chronic fatigue syndrome
OL,9,F"improved care closer to home" as it
OL,10,Facknowledged that many patients with
OL,11,Fthe condition "struggle" to get
OL,12,Fappropriate care.
OL,14,FThe Department of Health and Social
OL,15,FCare said it is "committed to changing
OL,16,Fattitudes and transforming care" for
OL,17,Fpeople with Myalgic Encephalomyelitis/
OL,18,F Chronic Fatigue Syndrome (ME/CFS) as
OL,19,Fit prepared to publish a new plan to
OL,20,Fimprove care for people with the
OL,21,Fcondition.
