OL,3,CGovernment pledges to 'transform care'
OL,4,Cfor people with ME
OL,6,FThe 10-day hearing focused on the
OL,7,Ffinal few months of her life, by which
OL,8,Ftime she was confined to bed, unable
OL,9,Fto chew food and had difficulty
OL,10,Fdrinking because she was not able to
OL,11,Fsit up.
OL,13,FMiss Boothby-O'Neill, the daughter of
OL,14,FSean O'Neill, a journalist with The
OL,15,FTimes newspaper, had been suffering
OL,16,Ffrom fatigue since the age of 13,
OL,17,Fwhich got worse after she completed
OL,18,Fher A-levels.
