OL,3,CGovernment pledges to 'transform care'
OL,4,Cfor people with ME
OL,6,FDeborah Archer, now an area coroner
OL,7,Ffor Devon, Plymouth and Torbay,
OL,8,Fconcluded Miss Boothby-O'Neill had
OL,9,Fdied from natural causes "because of
OL,10,Fsevere myalgic encephalomyelitis (ME)".
OL,12,FLast year she wrote to the Government
OL,13,Fto highlight a lack of specialist
OL,14,Fbeds, "extremely limited" training for
OL,15,Fdoctors and lack of available funding
OL,16,Ffor research and treatment of the
OL,17,Fcondition.
